H=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A Proposal for Planar Scheduling</span><hr size=1> Saph, actually the non-American guilds are pretty well known.<br>
<br>
As far as off-hour players are concerned, they do tend to hunt with non-American guild members alot. Even tho they would not be able to reserve a date themselves under this plan, I see no reason why they would not be invited along on these raids.<br>
<br>
Why not FCFS or FFA on a couple of days? The thing that makes reservations such a good thing is being able to take the time to get sign-ups and form a well balanced multi-group raiding party. Then, once the party is formed you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  know </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that the plane will be popped and available for you. If one opens it up to FCFS, you do not know that there will be anything there when you zone in.<br>
<br>
Why is the schedual on a monthly system and not every 5 weeks or so? This simply makes it easier to figure out for the mods.<br>
<br>
Why not let anyone reserve a 2-day block if they wish? See above. Plus, a two-day non-American block should be able to be split between Europian and Asian raids with little to no conflict. <br>
<br>
Why &quot;special treatment&quot; for off-hour/non-American players? Just go to any high level area in Kunark or Velious on off-peak times. The lack of Planer Armor and Epics speaks tells the tale of our current reservations system not working for them. <br>
<br>
Why not leave it as it is and let Asian raids end at 10am PST? Uber guilds can clear Fear in 2hrs. Armor crews take 6-10hrs or more. The majority of SK Armor drops from Temple Pulls. I have never been on a raid where time is running late and a suggestion of pulling Jellos has not kept most of the raiders in place, even if other MoBs are passed over. Making a system that allows Asians to clear the zone is fair. Telling them that they will not have the time to do that is unfair, IMO.<br>
<br>
Why these changes now and not months ago? Simply, server population. Only in the last few months has the server population risen to the numbers and levels for off-peak hour times that Planer raids during those times are feasable. Now, IMO, the reservation system must bend somehow to accomodate this change.<br>
<br>
Krungle Eisenguss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Administrator </font><br><font color=#A0B0E0>Burn the Witch! </font></span><br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/22/01 7:16:44 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A Proposal for Planar Scheduling</span><hr size=1> Saphdia: I am allowing ANY group that wants to to signup in the same fashion to do this.   If you start your raid after Midnight PST, and end before 10 AM PST, I'll allow you to sign up the day before, so that you don't come up to an empty plane.<br>
<br>
Basically, you're reserving for the evening PST on one date, plus 3-5 hours.  It happens to fall on the next &quot;date&quot; in PST, but it's basically the same as a very late starting PST raid.<br>
<br>
Thor: Your comment that the plane is &quot;Wasted&quot; for the 21st is incorrect.  Between the 20th, &amp; 23rd, mobs in Fear will be killed 4 times.  Once on the 20th, not on the 21st, early am 22nd, late evening 22nd/early am 23rd, and then the 23rd.  Regularly, that would have been evening 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd PST.<br>
<br>
Just because it's not the same way doesn't mean the mobs aren't getting killed as much.  If you want to be technical, mobs are &quot;wasting&quot; every time they're not killed as they spawn.  The average Fear mob will waste for maybe as much as 10 hours on average.<br>
<br>
To say that the 21 is being wasted is like saying that the planes go to waste every time that they're up for the Europeans in the evening &amp; they don't kill them.  I mean, they could have gone up during our afternoon &amp; done them.  But then Evening PST raids would have gone up to an empty plane.  In the same sense, it might seem as wasteage to you, because you're nobody's clearing the plane when you normally do, but a few hours later, Zenith will be there clearing the mobs. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umcx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>McX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/22/01 8:27:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A Proposal for Planar Scheduling</span><hr size=1> Am I the only one who sees that Fear and Hate are very underused zones under our current system?<br>
<br>
Adun, your proposal does waste a whole day.  It simply makes people utilize a zone efficiently the next day to make up for it.<br>
<br>
How about making shifts of 18 hours instead of using calaneder days?  Only rules are that you cant start your raid after the previous one ends, and you have to be out by the time your 'shift&quot; is scheduled to end.  You could maintain controll of this by pre posting the threads for each 'shift' in advance.  The first person to post to the thread no sooner than 2 weeks in advance without editing the post gets that shift.  They would be required to post the approx start and end time of their shift at the time of their reservation attempt, so that the following people would be able to determine whether or not the next shift would be spawned for them.  This would create more avail raids, would keep the start times in a constant state of change, giving advantage to different people all the time.<br>
<br>
<br>
